es of how we think about industry and place, and the political processes that have enabled a new paradigm in urban planning. Mixing urban sociology with media and cultural studies, Banks offers a lively account of how urban life and development are changing in the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAuthenticity (Philosophy). 0aCity planningxEconomic aspectszNew York (State)zUpstate New York. 0aSocial mediazNew York (State)zUpstate New YorkxInfluence. 0aUrbanizationxEconomic aspectszNew York (State)zUpstate New York. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Technology Studies.2bisacsh  adoing it for the gram.  ageography.  ainfluencers.  ainstagram.  arust belt cities.  asmall city.  asocial media gentrification.  asociology of urban development.  atechnology and urban life.  aupstate new york.  aurban planning.  aurban studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520383470?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520383470423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520383470/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131910-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PAC